<span id="freeTextContainer16643354708504704671">Much of his work has vanished, but Mas&apos;udi&apos;s matchless <i>The Meadows of Gold</i> has almost miraculously survived: a compendium of stories and information on what he knew of the worlds of the Middle East, the Far East and Europe. It is both a great monument to Islamic scholarship and a time capsule allowing us into the world over a millennium ago.</span>
