<div id="review_1317437569" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1317437569" />
    <a title="El-Jahiz" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21237727-el-jahiz"><img alt="El-Jahiz" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1371588085p2/21237727.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1317437569?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="El-Jahiz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="El-Jahiz" href="/user/show/21237727-el-jahiz">El-Jahiz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780710302465" href="/book/show/677509.Meadows_Of_Gold">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1317437569" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2300614367962968646">This volume from the Meadows of Gold by Al-Masudi, the Herodotus of the Arabs (9th century) is an excellent translation by Paul Lunde and Caroline Stone. Probably captures the true essence of the masterpiece in presenting the time of the Abbasiad Caliphs through a collage of anecdotes woven together that flows like poetry. Wish they also translated the rest of this enchanting book. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

